segments.title: Generative AI and Foundation Models
segments.summary: Introduces generative AI and foundation models, including large language models. Explains how these models can predict and generate entire documents rather than just single words.

segments.title: Understanding Generative Content Creation
segments.summary: Addresses the debate about whether generative AI truly creates new content, using a music analogy to explain how it combines existing information in novel ways to create something new.

segments.title: Types of Generative Models
segments.summary: Discusses different types of generative AI models including audio and video models, and their applications in creating deep fakes and voice recreation.

segments.title: Gen AI Impact
segments.summary: Describes how foundation models and generative AI have dramatically accelerated AI adoption compared to earlier AI technologies.
